Advanced English Dictionary



Advanced English Dictionary is distinguished from the other (paper, electronic) 

dictionaries in many ways. Not because it contains far more words than a conventional 

paper dictionary, but because it uses a radically new approach and technology called 

WordNet. Instead of just listing the words and their definitions, Advanced English 

Dictionary shows how every word is linked to another. Type in the word ÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã…â€œtreeÃƒÂ¢Ã¢â€šÂ¬Ã‚ï¿½ and you 

will get not only the definition, synonyms and opposites, but the hypernyms (a tree 

is a kind of what?), meronyms (what are the parts of a tree?) and more. You can also 

find a list of hundreds of trees, from yellowwood to the Tree of Knowledge, and even 

all words that contain the letters t-r-e-e. This WordNet approach will help you to 

understand better the meaning of words. Linguists call WordNet project one of the 

biggest leaps for dictionaries since scholars sat down to write the epic Oxford 

English Dictionary.
